C;DEFENSIVE FIRST FIRE PRINCIPLES;dffp;
T;<b>FIRST FIRE</b>
T;<b>Restriction:</b> Target must be moving, defender must not have a First Fire or Final Fire marker.
T;<b>Penalty:</b> None.
T;<b>Result:</b> Place a First Fire marker on defender, but not on any weapon that retains its ROF.
O;
T;<b>SUBSEQUENT FIRST FIRE</b>
T;<b>Restriction:</b> Target must be moving, there must not be any other known enemy units closer to the defender,and the defender must not have a Final Fire marker.
T;<b>Penalty: </b>Area Fire (½ FP), Sustained Fire (no ROF, B# –2, original B# becomes X#).
T;<b>Result: </b>Place Final Fire marker on defender and any SW/Guns defender possesses (even if those SW/Guns were not previously marked, and even if those SW/Guns did not fire with the squad).
T;
T;<b>FINAL PROTECTIVE FIRE</b>
T;<b>Restriction: </b>Target must have moved ADJACENT to defender.
T;<b>Penalty:</b> MGs must fire, Area Fire, Sustained Fire, IFT DR is also a NMC roll for the defender.
T;<b>Result:</b> Final Fire marker remains on defender and any SW/Guns defender possesses, unless the defender fails he NMC and breaks.
